SIMPLE: shallow
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shallow
<hw>Shal"low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Shallower</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Shallowest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>schalowe</ets>, probably originally, sloping or shelving; cf. Icel.
<ets>skj⟦amac⟧lgr</ets> wry, squinting, AS. <ets>sceolh</ets>, D. & G.
<ets>scheel</ets>, OHG. <ets>schelah</ets>. Cf. <er>Shelve</er> to
slope, <er>Shoal</er> shallow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not deep; having
little depth; shoal.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Shallow</xex> brooks, and rivers
wide.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not deep in tone.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sound perfecter and not so <qex>shallow</qex> and jarring.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not intellectually deep; not profound; not
penetrating deeply; simple; not wise or knowing; ignorant; superficial;
<as>as, a <ex>shallow</ex> mind; <ex>shallow</ex>
learning</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The king was neither so <qex>shallow</qex>, nor so ill advertised,
as not to perceive the intention of the French king.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Deep versed in books, and <qex>shallow</qex> in himself.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shallow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shallow
<hw>Shal"low</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place in a body of
water where the water is not deep; a shoal; a flat; a shelf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A swift stream is not heard in the channel, but upon
<qex>shallows</qex> of gravel.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dashed on the <qex>shallows</qex> of the moving sand.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The rudd.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shallow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shallow
<hw>Shal"low</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make shallow.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shallow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Shallow
<hw>Shal"low</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become shallow, as
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shallow-bodied</ent>⟦br⟧
